The paper discusses the use of telecommunication technologies for remote monitoring of patients during ambulance transport, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the collection of geographical and communication traces, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The focus on remote monitoring of critically ill patients suggests a potential overlap with the healthcare (cs.HC) and human-computer interaction (cs.OH) categories. Finally, the paper mentions the transmission of clinical multimedia, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
